		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Charge of the Light Brigade</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Charge_of_the_Light_Brigade_(disambiguation)" title="Charge of the Light Brigade (disambiguation)">Charge of the Light Brigade (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="metadata plainlinks topicon" id="protected-icon" style="position:absolute; z-index:100; right:55px; top:10px;">
<div><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#move" title="This article is move-protected due to vandalism."><img alt="Move protected" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Padlock-olive.svg/20px-Padlock-olive.svg.png" width="20" height="20" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:CatonWoodvilleLightBrigade.jpeg" class="image" title="Charge of the Light Brigade by Richard Caton Woodville (1825-1855)"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/CatonWoodvilleLightBrigade.jpeg/300px-CatonWoodvilleLightBrigade.jpeg" width="300" height="171" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:CatonWoodvilleLightBrigade.jpeg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<i>Charge of the Light Brigade</i> by <a href="/wiki/Richard_Caton_Woodville" title="Richard Caton Woodville">Richard Caton Woodville</a> (1825-1855)</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Charge of the Light Brigade</b> was a disastrous <a href="/wiki/Charge_(warfare)" title="Charge (warfare)">charge</a> of British <a href="/wiki/Cavalry" title="Cavalry">cavalry</a> led by <a href="/wiki/James_Brudenell,_7th_Earl_of_Cardigan" title="James Brudenell, 7th Earl of Cardigan">Lord Cardigan</a> against Russian forces during the <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Balaclava" title="Battle of Balaclava">Battle of Balaclava</a> on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1854-10-25"><a href="/wiki/October_25" title="October 25">25 October</a> <a href="/wiki/1854" title="1854">1854</a></span> in the <a href="/wiki/Crimean_War" title="Crimean War">Crimean War</a>. It is best remembered as the subject of a famous poem entitled <i><a href="/wiki/The_Charge_of_the_Light_Brigade_(poem)" title="The Charge of the Light Brigade (poem)">The Charge of the Light Brigade</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Alfred_Lord_Tennyson" title="Alfred Lord Tennyson" class="mw-redirect">Alfred, Lord Tennyson</a>, whose lines have made the charge a symbol of warfare at both its most courageous and its most tragic.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
<tr>
<td>
